			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Just Played EQII<a name="56746"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 14 04 10:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well I'm down here at QuakeCon in Texas and happen to notice a EQII beta running.. All I can say is WOW.. I'm loving it..
<br />

<br />
I can't wait for it..
<br />

<br />
I only made it to level 5 with a mage and fighter but both were fun to play.. Qeynos is huge.. Some inner city quest use the path tool like the bazaar find tool.. Interacting with NPC is FUN and easy as now it's a menu system instead of text keywords.
<br />

<br />
As a level 5 fighter I had a badass looking two-hand sword (black with gold tribal graphics in it).. Quest not have a log with checkboxes telling you what you did and what you still need to do.
<br />

<br />
The GUI needs help/work but other then that the game play was amazing.
<br />

<br />
Well since I'm not tied down by any EULA (I didn't log in or agree to anything down here) I figured I would release some info..
<br />

<br />
P.S. Leveling to 5 takes some work.. Not like EQI.. I talked to an nvidia guy and he said leveling to 20 should take around 100 hours but if they are anything like the 1st 5 I wont mind one bit..</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
