			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just Played EQII<a name="56752"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 14 04 11:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can count on NOTHING when in beta..  But I gotta admit the 1st 5 levels were fun, more fun then in EQI. Also Norath is NOTHING like EQI.. I was worried it would be just a new face on an old game but thats just not the case.. Half the time I was lost.. Qeynos is now more or less an island with a moot kind of river around the front..
<br />

<br />
Also when you target something it tells you the level as well as mouseovers give a con system.. The name color is the mobs con and if it has a glowing red around it it is KOS..
<br />

<br />
The fighting action is amazing.. WHen you dodge you guy really dodges and it's not always the same animation.. I haven't seen you jump over a strike yet but I have seen mobs duck them..
<br />

<br />
The boot ride in the beginning (everyone starts on one I think) was a blast.. The water looks as real as any game I have every seen and has swells as big as the boat.. This is also where you get your 1st look at a dragon (Although just a basic brown one) that tries to attack the boat..
<br />

<br />
Expect to upgrade your systems to play though.. Inside Qeynos was a little chopped on an Alienware P4 3.06, 1gig DDR 800mgz FSB 6800 Ultra and a raptor drive.. BUt other then in the city it was very smooth. If I had to rate this beta against other beta I have been in this one rules them all.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
