				<td colspan="2"><span>Wow, i dunno about this 72 man zerg thing.
<br />

<br />
Play some high end large raid fights before you say that.
<br />

<br />
The rathe council is a good example of an event that requires all 72+ players to cooperate in an amazingly complex scenario over the course of several hours.  And yes, one person not paying attn for a few mins in that scenario often causes the entire raid to wipe and end the event.
<br />

<br />
The large raid events in PoP are amazing in their variety of encounters and the degree of cooperation required to pull them off.
<br />

<br />
I guess i worry about eq2 being a &quot;dumbed down&quot; version of eq1.  Lots of tactics used now in eq have been removed from the game, and I wonder how much difference there really is between a mage and a warrior?  As much as in eq1? Too much emphasis on making subclasses versatile enough to fit in a group equally well and fulfill all the needs of that group.</span></td>
