				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
I don't think the comment was &quot;in 72 person raids you do nothing&quot;... I think it was just sorta a generalization that as the raid sizes get bigger... on a lot of encounters, many players COULD afk at times... trash dies really quick... etc... most people don't afk during boss fights.
<br />

<br />
Its just the idea that lets say... you're 1 of 6 bards on a raid.    Even though everyone loves you.... you're maybe not critical to a particular raid.
<br />

<br />
But if we dropped you to the only bard on a raid... your role becomes more important, and if you afk, people notice that they're getting no benifit from their bard.
<br />

<br />
So going from a 72 person raid with lots of skill overlap, down to a 24 person raid... it's more likly that everyone on that raid will be very important, and can't slack off much.
<br />
</span></td>
