			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just Played EQII<a name="57089"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
Less people doesn't mean anything was dumbed down.
<br />

<br />
4 healers for a 1000 hitting mob, is the same as 2 healers on a 500 hitting mob.    Depending on how long the fight is, both cases can be equally &quot;hard&quot;.   
<br />

<br />
I haven't played EQ2, and I certainly haven't raided in EQ2.... but what I hear is that each person's contribution will mean more to the raid.    If you suck, it will mean more.  If you rock, it will mean more.
<br />

<br />
Will it?  I dunno yet, but I'll find out when it release and people start to raid.
<br />

<br />
There's room there for hardcore raiders.  I think the whole point is not to require a 72 person guild (thats just the online people) in order to do stuff.     It's much easier for a 24 person guild/raid to form.
<br />

<br />
If PoP was balanced around 24 people... more casual type people could give it a better chance.  It would still be HARD for them because they wouldn't be geared like the ubers coming out of the previous expansions... but it's easier to get 24 people than 72.   So they could have worked on the content without always making it a pickup raid.
<br />

<br />
Another huge plus in the game, is the lack of dependance on clerics.   They promise that any Priest can do the job.   So if you only have 1 cleric, 2 shamans, and a druid on... you should be able to do any job that 4 clerics could do.    This alone will make raiding much more fun.     My last guild on Quellious often had 30-40 people online, but 1 regular cleric... that really hurt what we could do... and was a real mental drain too sometimes to see so many people on , and 1 cleric.   (We subbed druids in at times, and that worked sometimes).
<br />

<br />
I can't wait to play it.   I feel that it will do away with SOME bs from Everquest... make the game more accessable to people... and I'm sure some of the encounters will be just as hard, if not harder, than EQ 1... you just won't have to find 100 people, 37 of which are clerics, to do it.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
