				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just Played EQII<a name="57091"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 10:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I guess i worry about eq2 being a &quot;dumbed down&quot; version of eq1. Lots of tactics used now in eq have been removed from the game, and I wonder how much difference there really is between a mage and a warrior? As much as in eq1? Too much emphasis on making subclasses versatile enough to fit in a group equally well and fulfill all the needs of that group.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Well my comments can only take you to level 5 but I can tell you that the mage class becomes dependant on magic very early.. I was doing the root and nuke by the time I hit level 5 cause standing toe to toe no longer was an option.. My fighter seem to tank like a king. Taunt worked from a distance now and can be used for pulling.
<br />

<br />
Again I don't know what it's going to be like later on but if they both start to fill their roles and take their paths as early as level 5 I wouldn't worry too much about later levels.
<br />

<br />
If I had to guess I would say the game took alot from DAoC and improved on it. Steath and Sneak work the same. Your toom becomes nothing more then a shadow. Since I didn't play a rogue I'm only guessing but it seems if a mob is higher level then you it can see you better then lower level mobs (just like DAoC)..
<br />

<br />
Thinks I left out:
<br />
1) You no longer need to loot quest items. I'm guessing but I think everyone in the group that needs the quest items gets it (like DAoC)..
<br />
2) When you kill a mob normal vendor loot it in the corpse but if they have a item a chest pops on the corpse with the item inside it.
<br />
3) You seem to get good items young. My fighter had a 19AC chestplate with 3STR.. Anyone know played EQ in the beginning knows what was NOT the case in EQ.
<br />
4) Items get better with levels. The sword I was using was a 3-7 damage at level 5 and a 4-12 at level 10. (Says it on the item)
<br />
5) When you die you items need to be repaired but EVERYONE has a repairing skill so they can fix their own items with a kit. More or less a money sink to keep plat out of the game.
<br />
6) When you die you select you respawn point. I think it's a list of the town you have been to cause mine only had two towns and only was in two towns.
<br />
7) When you die you respawn with ALL your gear but level some kind of soulstone.. Not really sure what it is yet but my 1st guess would be like a gravestone in DAoC.. Get your soulstone and maybe you gain exp back.
<br />
8) Your spells are now on a toolbar more like your hotkey bank.. You have like 10 pages of them so looks like there is no need to swap out spells anymore. Again alot like DAoC..
<br />

<br />
Well thats all I can think of right now. If I think of more I'll let you know..</span></td>
