				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just Played EQII<a name="57113"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 12:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>From the Sony site, you have something like 5 soulstones and having all of them means you have some ability or degree of skill in something -- that's not clear in my memory.  If you leave a soulstone somewhere after dying, you are impaired by that to some extent until you either 1) go back and pick it up or 2) gradually regain it through XP.  So it is not a chunk of XP like in DAOC nor is it an XP debt like in COH.  It is a temporary loss of ability that you can go back and recover immediately, or eventually recover normally.  But in either case, it doesn't ding your XP bar and it doesn't represent permanant damage to your toon.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
